                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten or thirty
                           separated by a crude zigzag, drawn in pencil. Also, a zigzag occurs at
                           the beginning of Text I-2.&#xD; - Indication concerning the special
                           occasions when Ps. 3 could be read: ሶበ፡ ትፈቱ፡ ሢመተ፡ አንብብ፡ ለርእሰከ፡ is
                           written, in a secondary hand, in ink, on <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.
                           &#xD; - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the
                           whole line: <locus target="#123v">123v</locus>, 124v, 125r, 126rv, 132r,
                           138r.&#xD; - Part of the line is taken up: e.g., <locus target="#9r"
                              >9r</locus>, 34r, 52r, 64v, 72r, 78v, 81v, 87v, 91r, 97v, 99v, 145v,
                           150r, 157r, 163v, 165v.&#xD; - Part of the line is taken down: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>, 39r, 46v, 64r, 78r, 81r, 100v,
                           101v.&#xD; - Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross, indicating the place
                           where the omission, written in the upper margin, belongs: <locus
                              target="#56v">56v</locus> l.10.&#xD; - Numerous corrections written
                           over erasures, most probably in a secondary hand: e.g., <locus
                              target="#5r">5r</locus>, 15r, 20r, 34v, 53v, 65r, 81v, 90v, 109v,
                           121v, 152v.&#xD; - Erasures marked with two or three lines: e.g., <locus
                              target="#9v">9v</locus>, 14v, 21v, 24r, 37r, 57v, 60v, 79r, 88v,
                           133r.&#xD; - Line or several lines of a text have been rubbed out: <locus
                              from="152r" to="153v">152r-153v</locus>, 161v, 176ra, 177rb.&#xD; - A
                           few lines of Ps. 1 are written on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. &#xD; -
